# Astro Styles

Best practices for styling Astro components with scoped CSS and style management.

<rule>
name: astro_styles
description: Standards for CSS and styling in Astro components
filters:
  - type: file_extension
    pattern: "\\.astro$"
  - type: content
    pattern: "<style>"

actions:
  - type: suggest
    message: |
      Follow these best practices for styling Astro components:

      ## Scoped Styles by Default

      Astro automatically scopes styles to the component.

      ```astro
      ---
      interface Props {
        title: string;
      }
      const { title } = Astro.props;
      ---
      
      <article>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
      </article>
      
      <style>
        /* ✅ Automatically scoped to this component */
        article {
          max-width: 800px;
          margin: 0 auto;
        }
        
        h1 {
          color: var(--color-primary);
          font-size: 2rem;
        }
      </style>
      ```

      ## Best Practices

      ### 1. Use CSS Custom Properties for Theming
      ```astro
      <style>
        /* ✅ GOOD: Use CSS variables */
        .card {
          background: var(--card-bg, #ffffff);
          border: 1px solid var(--card-border, #e5e7eb);
          padding: var(--spacing-4, 1rem);
        }
        
        /* ❌ BAD: Hard-coded values */
        .card {
          background: #ffffff;
          border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
          padding: 1rem;
        }
      </style>
      ```

      ### 2. Scope Styles Appropriately
      ```astro
      <!-- ✅ GOOD: Scoped styles (default) -->
      <style>
        .button {
          /* Only affects this component */
        }
      </style>
      
      <!-- ✅ GOOD: Global styles when needed -->
      <style is:global>
        /* Affects entire page */
        body {
          font-family: system-ui;
        }
      </style>
      
      <!-- ✅ GOOD: Mix scoped and global -->
      <style>
        /* Scoped */
        .container {
          padding: 1rem;
        }
        
        /* Global within container */
        :global(.container p) {
          margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }
      </style>
      ```

      ### 3. Inline Styles for Dynamic Values
      ```astro
      ---
      interface Props {
        backgroundColor: string;
        size: number;
      }
      const { backgroundColor, size } = Astro.props;
      ---
      
      <!-- ✅ GOOD: Dynamic inline styles -->
      <div style={`background-color: ${backgroundColor}; width: ${size}px;`}>
        Content
      </div>
      ```

      ### 4. Class Composition
      ```astro
      ---
      interface Props {
        variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary';
        size?: 'sm' | 'lg';
        class?: string;
      }
      
      const { 
        variant = 'primary', 
        size = 'sm',
        class: className 
      } = Astro.props;
      
      const classes = [
        'button',
        `button-${variant}`,
        `button-${size}`,
        className
      ].filter(Boolean).join(' ');
      ---
      
      <button class={classes}>
        <slot />
      </button>
      
      <style>
        .button {
          padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
          border: none;
          border-radius: 0.25rem;
          cursor: pointer;
        }
        
        .button-primary {
          background: var(--color-primary);
          color: white;
        }
        
        .button-secondary {
          background: var(--color-secondary);
          color: white;
        }
      </style>
      ```

      ### 5. Use Tailwind When Available
      ```astro
      ---
      // If project uses Tailwind, prefer it for utility styles
      ---
      
      <!-- ✅ GOOD: Tailwind for common styles -->
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4">
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">
          {title}
        </h1>
      </div>
      ```

examples:
  - input: |
      # Bad: Hard-coded, unscoped
      <style is:global>
        .btn { background: #3b82f6; }
      </style>
      
      # Good: Scoped, themed
      <style>
        .button {
          background: var(--color-primary);
          padding: var(--spacing-2);
        }
      </style>
    output: "Well-organized scoped styles"
</rule>
